1. System Scope

The Real Estate Business Database System will manage the daily activities of a real estate company. It will allow administrators and agents to manage property listings, property owners, customers, property visits, sales, rentals, and payments. The system will also generate reports and maintain audit logs to improve security and accountability.

The system covers:
Property registration
Property owner management
Customer registration
Real estate agent management
Property visits
Property sales
Property rentals
Payment management
Report generation
Audit logging
2. Actors
Actor	Responsibility
Administrator	Manages users, database, reports, and security
Real Estate Agent	Registers properties, owners, customers, visits, sales, and rentals
Property Owner	Provides property information to the agency
Customer	Buys or rents properties
Manager	Reviews reports and monitors business performance
3. Main Business Processes
Property Registration
Register a property owner.
Add a new property.
Assign the property to an agent.
Customer Registration
Register a customer.
Store customer contact information.
Property Visit
Customer requests a visit.
Agent schedules the visit.
Visit record is stored.
Property Sale
Customer chooses a property.
Agent confirms availability.
Sale is recorded.
Payment is recorded.
Property status changes to Sold.
Property Rental
Customer selects a rental property.
Rental agreement is created.
Payment is recorded.
Property status changes to Rented.
Reporting
Generate sales reports.
Generate rental reports.
Generate payment reports.
Generate property availability reports.
