7. One-Page Explanation

The Real Estate Business Database System is designed to improve the management of properties, customers, property owners, agents, sales, rentals, and payments. The process begins when a property owner registers a property with the real estate company. A real estate agent records the property details in the database, making it available for sale or rent.

Customers register before requesting to view available properties. Agents schedule property visits, and after viewing, customers may choose to buy or rent a property. The system records all sales or rental agreements, stores payment information, and automatically updates the property's availability status.

Administrators oversee user accounts, security, and reporting, while managers use generated reports to monitor company performance. Every important database activity is audited to enhance security and accountability. This workflow ensures accurate records, reduces manual work, and improves customer service.
